---
import DocsLayout from '../../layouts/DocsLayout.astro';
---

<DocsLayout title="Session Management">
  <h1>Session Management</h1>
  <p>
    EncodeSwarmr issues a session token on login that is stored as a browser cookie. The session management API lets users view and revoke their own active sessions. Users can only see and revoke sessions that belong to their own account — the ownership check is enforced server-side before any deletion.
  </p>

  <h2>Session model</h2>
  <table>
    <thead>
      <tr><th>Field</th><th>Type</th><th>Description</th></tr>
    </thead>
    <tbody>
      <tr>
        <td><code>user_id</code></td>
        <td>string</td>
        <td>ID of the user this session belongs to.</td>
      </tr>
      <tr>
        <td><code>ip_address</code></td>
        <td>string</td>
        <td>IP address from which the session was created.</td>
      </tr>
      <tr>
        <td><code>user_agent</code></td>
        <td>string</td>
        <td>Browser user-agent string recorded at login.</td>
      </tr>
      <tr>
        <td><code>created_at</code></td>
        <td>timestamp</td>
        <td>UTC timestamp when the session was created.</td>
      </tr>
      <tr>
        <td><code>expires_at</code></td>
        <td>timestamp</td>
        <td>UTC timestamp when the session expires. Expired sessions are excluded from the list.</td>
      </tr>
    </tbody>
  </table>
  <p>
    The raw session token is excluded from all API responses (<code>json:"-"</code>). It is transmitted only as an <code>HttpOnly</code> cookie and is never returned in JSON payloads.
  </p>

  <h3>Session TTL</h3>
  <p>Session lifetime is configured via <code>auth.session_ttl</code> in the controller YAML:</p>
  <pre><code>auth:
  session_ttl: 24h   # default; accepts Go duration strings, e.g. 8h, 7d</code></pre>
  <p>Sessions that have passed their <code>expires_at</code> are automatically excluded from list results.</p>

  <h2>API</h2>

  <h3>List sessions</h3>
  <pre><code>GET /api/v1/sessions</code></pre>
  <p><strong>Required role:</strong> <code>viewer</code> (own sessions only)</p>
  <p>Returns all unexpired sessions for the authenticated user, ordered by <code>created_at</code> descending.</p>
  <p><strong>Response:</strong></p>
  <pre><code>[
  &#123;
    "user_id": "usr_abc123",
    "ip_address": "10.0.1.42",
    "user_agent": "Mozilla/5.0 (Windows NT 10.0; Win64; x64) ...",
    "created_at": "2026-03-24T09:00:00Z",
    "expires_at": "2026-03-25T09:00:00Z"
  &#125;
]</code></pre>
  <p>The token field is never included in the response.</p>
  <p><strong>Example:</strong></p>
  <pre><code>curl -s https://controller.example.com/api/v1/sessions \
  -H "Cookie: session=&lt;token&gt;"</code></pre>

  <h3>Revoke a session</h3>
  <pre><code>DELETE /api/v1/sessions/&#123;id&#125;</code></pre>
  <p><strong>Required role:</strong> <code>viewer</code> (own sessions only)</p>
  <p>
    Revokes the session identified by <code>&#123;id&#125;</code>. The server verifies that the session belongs to the authenticated user before deleting it. Attempting to delete a session that belongs to a different user returns <code>404 Not Found</code> — the same response given for a non-existent session, to avoid leaking session existence.
  </p>
  <p><strong>Response (success):</strong></p>
  <pre><code>&#123;"ok": true&#125;</code></pre>
  <p><strong>Response (not found or wrong owner):</strong> <code>404 Not Found</code></p>
  <p><strong>Example:</strong></p>
  <pre><code>curl -s -X DELETE https://controller.example.com/api/v1/sessions/&lt;session-id&gt; \
  -H "Cookie: session=&lt;token&gt;"</code></pre>
  <p>Revoking your own current session will immediately invalidate your login. The next request will receive a <code>401 Unauthorized</code> response.</p>

  <h2>UI walkthrough</h2>
  <p>Users manage their sessions from the <strong>Profile</strong> page:</p>
  <ol>
    <li>Click the avatar in the top-right corner and select <strong>Profile</strong>.</li>
    <li>Navigate to the <strong>Sessions</strong> tab.</li>
    <li>The table lists active sessions with columns for login time, IP address, user agent, and expiry time.</li>
    <li>Click <strong>Terminate</strong> on any row to revoke that session immediately.</li>
    <li>A confirmation dialog appears before the revocation is sent. Confirm to proceed.</li>
  </ol>
  <p>Terminating the current session will log you out immediately.</p>
</DocsLayout>
